<h4>Identity validation method:</h4>
<br />
<div>
    <div class="form-check">
        <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="methodRadio" id="methodRadioEmail" checked>
        <label class="form-check-label" for="methodRadioEmail">
            <i class="bi bi-envelope"></i> E-Mail
        </label>
    </div>
    <div class="fst-italic small">
        If you choose the authentication method via e-mail, you will receive an e-mail with a confirmation code, 
        that you will have to enter in the next step. 
        If you do not receive a message, please consider checking your spam folder.
    </div>
</div>
<br />
<div>
    <div class="form-check">
        <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="methodRadio" id="methodRadioLogin">
        <label class="form-check-label" for="methodRadioLogin">
            <i class="bi bi-person"></i> Login
        </label>
    </div>
    <div class="fst-italic small">
        If you have an account for this service, you can verify yourself using your login credentials.
    </div>
</div>
<br />
<div>
    <div class="form-check">
        <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="methodRadio" id="methodRadioCertificate">
        <label class="form-check-label" for="methodRadioCertificate">
            <i class="bi bi-person"></i> Certificate
        </label>
    </div>
    <div class="fst-italic small">
        You can provide a certificate and a password to sign cryptographically. 
        If your are not comfortable uploading your certificate and your password, you can use LIONS Certificates Wallet instead.
    </div>
</div>
<br />
<div>
    <div class="form-check">
        <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="methodRadio" id="methodRadioWallet">
        <label class="form-check-label" for="methodRadioWallet">
            <i class="bi bi-person"></i> LIONS Certificates Wallet
        </label>
    </div>
    <div class="fst-italic small">
        You can use the certificates wallet to store your certificates and authenticate and sign locally on your device keeping your private key private.
    </div>
</div>
<br />
<div style="display:none"> <!-- hidden ! -->
    <div class="form-check">
        <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="methodRadio" id="methodRadioSMS">
        <label class="form-check-label" for="methodRadioSMS">
            <i class="bi bi-phone"></i> SMS
        </label>
    </div>
    <div class="fst-italic small">
        If you choose the authentication method via SMS, you will receive an SMS with a confirmation code, 
        that you will have to enter in the next step.
    </div>
</div>
<br />
<div>
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary w-100" onclick="methodFormSubmit()">Next</button>
</div>